Class Type<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.syst3ms.skriptparser.types.Type<T>

  • public class Type<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A basic definition of a type. This doesn't handle number (single/plural), unlike PatternType

      • Type

        public Type(java.lang.Class<T> typeClass,
            java.lang.String baseName,
            java.lang.String pattern)
        Constructs a new Type.
        Parameters:
        typeClass - the class this type represents
        baseName - the basic name to represent this type with. It should be more or less a lowercase version of the Java class.
        pattern - the pattern for plural forms. It's written in Skript aliases plural format. Examples :
        • fish -> fish (invariant)
        • dog&brvbar;s -> dog and dogs
        • part&brvbar;y&brvbar;ies -> party and parties (irregular plural)

        Constructs a new Type.
        Parameters:
        typeClass - the class this type represents
        baseName - the basic name to represent this type with. It should be more or less a lowercase version of the Java class.
        pattern - the pattern for plural forms. It's written in Skript aliases plural format. Examples :
        • fish -> fish (invariant)
        • dog&brvbar;s -> dog and dogs
        • part&brvbar;y&brvbar;ies -> party and parties (irregular plural)
        literalParser - the function that would parse literals for the given type. If the parser throws an exception on parsing, it will be caught and the type will be ignored.

        public Type(java.lang.Class<T> typeClass,

        Constructs a new Type.
        Parameters:
        typeClass - the class this type represents
        baseName - the basic name to represent this type with. It should be more or less a lowercase version of the Java class.
        pattern - the pattern for plural forms. It's written in Skript aliases plural format. Examples :
        • fish -> fish (invariant)
        • dog&brvbar;s -> dog and dogs
        • part&brvbar;y&brvbar;ies -> party and parties (irregular plural)
        literalParser - the function that would parse literals for the given type. If the parser throws an exception on parsing, it will be caught and the type will be ignored.
        toStringFunction - the functions that converts an object of the type T to a String.Defaults to Objects.toString(java.lang.Object) for other constructors.
